114
00:11:38.061 --> 00:11:40.396
Please. I only know
what they tell me.

115
00:11:40.417 --> 00:11:43.525
And what they tell me
changes from day to day.

116
00:11:43.545 --> 00:11:47.007
Aren't you supposed
to be able to help?

117
00:11:47.132 --> 00:11:50.177
I mean, what if I just
took this thing off?

118
00:11:50.302 --> 00:11:51.990
What are they going
to do about it?

119
00:11:51.991 --> 00:11:53.013
They will shoot you.

120
00:11:53.138 --> 00:11:55.984
Why don't you stop
this silly talk?

121
00:11:55.985 --> 00:11:57.184
Itzhak Stern.

122
00:11:57.309 --> 00:12:00.479
I'm looking for Itzhak Stern.

123
00:12:02.022 --> 00:12:05.171
Are you Itzhak Stern or not?

124
00:12:05.192 --> 00:12:08.445
- I am.
- Where can we talk?

125
00:12:17.871 --> 00:12:21.959
There's a company you did the
books for, on Lipowa Street.

126
00:12:22.292 --> 00:12:24.461
Made what? Pots and pans?

127
00:12:24.482 --> 00:12:27.631
By law, I have to tell
you, sir, I'm a Jew.

128
00:12:27.756 --> 00:12:31.635
Well, I'm a German.
So there we are.

129
00:12:34.430 --> 00:12:38.142
- A good company, you think?
- Modestly successful.

130
00:12:38.267 --> 00:12:40.394
I know nothing about
enamelware. Do you?

131
00:12:40.415 --> 00:12:43.314
I was just the accountant.

132
00:12:43.439 --> 00:12:45.295
Simple engineering though,
wouldn't you think?

133
00:12:45.316 --> 00:12:46.963
Change the machines around,
whatever you do...

134
00:12:46.984 --> 00:12:49.570
you could make other
things, couldn't you?

135
00:12:49.591 --> 00:12:54.533
Field kits, mess kits.
Army contracts.

136
00:12:56.535 --> 00:12:58.892
Once the war ends, forget
it, but for now it's great.

137
00:12:58.912 --> 00:13:00.873
You can make a fortune,
don't you think?

138
00:13:00.894 --> 00:13:04.752
I think most people right
now have other priorities.

139
00:13:04.877 --> 00:13:07.755
Like what?

140
00:13:07.880 --> 00:13:10.049
I'm sure you'll do just fine,
once you get the contracts.

141
00:13:10.174 --> 00:13:12.134
In fact, the worse things
get, the better you'll do.

142
00:13:12.155 --> 00:13:15.929
Oh, well, I can get the signatures
I need. That's the easy part.

143
00:13:16.055 --> 00:13:19.725
Finding the money to buy
the company, that's hard.

144
00:13:19.808 --> 00:13:21.602
You don't have any money?

145
00:13:21.685 --> 00:13:25.939
Not that kind of money.
You know anybody?

146
00:13:27.316 --> 00:13:28.942
Jews, yeah.

147
00:13:29.068 --> 00:13:31.591
Investors. You must
have contacts...

148
00:13:31.674 --> 00:13:33.572
