What, if you don't mind
my asking, would you do?

161
00:14:09.692 --> 00:14:11.735
I'd make sure it's known
the company's in business.

162
00:14:11.819 --> 00:14:14.134
I'd see that it had
a certain panache.

163
00:14:14.217 --> 00:14:18.388
That's what I'm good at. Not
the work, not the work.

164
00:14:18.471 --> 00:14:20.869
The presentation.

165
00:14:38.887 --> 00:14:43.183
I'm sure I don't know anybody
who'll be interested in this.

166
00:14:44.560 --> 00:14:47.750
Well, they should
be, Itzhak Stern.

167
00:14:48.355 --> 00:14:51.254
Tell them they should be.

168
00:15:00.534 --> 00:15:02.807
Attention, attention.

169
00:15:02.828 --> 00:15:09.189
All Jews. From now on,
it's forbidden...

170
00:15:21.972 --> 00:15:25.726
I've got a client who'll sell
marks for zloty at 2.45 to 1.

171
00:15:25.851 --> 00:15:28.020
Wool, mink collar.
It's a nice coat.

172
00:15:28.103 --> 00:15:30.105
She'll trade it for
ration coupons.

173
00:15:30.189 --> 00:15:33.567
- Wicks, for lamps.
- You have a truckload of wicks?

174
00:15:33.692 --> 00:15:35.694
What am I going to do with
a truckload of wicks?

175
00:15:35.731 --> 00:15:37.696
