995
01:24:49.306 --> 01:24:52.023
What do you mean, you
can't forget it.

996
01:24:52.024 --> 01:24:53.748
It gives me a headache.

997
01:25:00.401 --> 01:25:03.883
- I couldn't get you out of here.
- I'll be all right.

998
01:25:03.967 --> 01:25:08.304
Anyway, I'm here almost every
week. Wednesdays, usually.

999
01:25:08.388 --> 01:25:11.954
I'll look in on you,
see how you're doing.

1000
01:25:13.288 --> 01:25:17.397
Here, put these in your pocket.

1001
01:25:17.480 --> 01:25:19.524
Come on.

1002
01:25:23.361 --> 01:25:28.032
Mr Director, don't let things
fall apart. I've worked too hard.

1003
01:25:36.332 --> 01:25:41.004
Thanks for... Good luck.

1004
01:26:02.212 --> 01:26:05.236
Attention. Caps off.

1005
01:26:14.830 --> 01:26:17.958
- Work.
- Back to work.

1006
01:26:31.554 --> 01:26:36.163
- What are you making?
- Hinges, sir.

1007
01:26:38.436 --> 01:26:40.274
Yeah, I've got some
workers coming in

1008
01:26:40.275 --> 01:26:42.065
tomorrow. Where are
they from again?

1009
01:26:42.148 --> 01:26:44.213
Yugoslavia, Mr Commander.

1010
01:26:44.296 --> 01:26:46.861
I've got to make room.

1011
01:26:49.322 --> 01:26:52.784
- Make me a hinge.
- Yes, sir.

1012
01:27:24.023 --> 01:27:27.235
Keep going, you're doing well.

1013
01:27:27.318 --> 01:27:29.404
Says he's doing well.

1014
01:27:36.077 --> 01:27:38.746
Oh, that's very good.

1015
01:27:38.830 --> 01:27:42.584
But I'm a bit confused, and
perhaps you can help me.

1016
01:27:42.667 --> 01:27:46.296
What I don't understand is
that you've been working...

1017
01:27:46.379 --> 01:27:50.925
since I think, what,
about 6.00 this morning?

1018
01:27:51.468 --> 01:27:56.097
Yet such a small pile of hinges.

1019
01:28:25.210 --> 01:28:28.213
- Oh, Christ.
- May I try that, sir?

1020
01:28:28.296 --> 01:28:30.465
Check the angle lever.
Maybe it's bent.

1021
01:28:30.548 --> 01:28:33.885
No, no. You wouldn't hear a click
if it was the angle lever.

1022
01:28:33.968 --> 01:28:36.450
- Maybe the pin shaft is greasy.
- Yeah, come on.

1023
01:28:36.533 --> 01:28:39.703
What did I just say? Here.

1024
01:28:42.498 --> 01:28:43.791
Mr Commander.

1025
01:28:43.832 --> 01:28:49.380
I beg to report that my heap of
hinges was so unsatisfactory...

1026
01:28:49.463 --> 01:28:53.488
because the machines were being
recalibrated this morning.

1027
01:28:55.240 --> 01:28:58.409
I was put on to shovelling coal.

1028
01:29:22.267 --> 01:29:24.352
Strange, huh?

1029
01:29:24.435 --> 01:29:26.396
Yeah.

1030
01:29:31.067 --> 01:29:34.362
Thank you, Muek.

1031
01:29:34.445 --> 01:29:38.158
Ah, Lisiek. Don't touch the
leather, it's just been oiled.

1032
01:29:38.241 --> 01:29:40.097
- Squad leader.
- Oh, for me?

1033
01:29:40.139 --> 01:29:42.883
Oh, thank you very
much, Mr Director.

1034
01:29:42.884 --> 01:29:43.913
Mr Director.

1035
01:29:43.997 --> 01:29:46.541
Mr Director.

1036
01:29:49.023 --> 01:29:51.671
Mr Director.

1037
01:29:53.548 --> 01:29:54.716
He was making hinges slowly.

1038
01:29:54.757 --> 01:29:57.559
So the man can turn
out a hinge in less

1039
01:29:57.560 --> 01:30:00.013
than a minute. Why the long story?

1040
01:30:28.771 --> 01:30:31.836
- Thank you, sir.
- You're welcome.

1041
01:30:35.006 --> 01:30:37.173
Nobody knows who
stole the chicken?

1042
01:30:37.174 --> 01:30:38.885
Tell him about the chicken.

1043
01:30:38.968 --> 01:30:43.765
A man walks around with a chicken
and nobody notices this.

1044
01:30:43.848 --> 01:30:46.434
Save yourselves.

1045
01:30:46.518 --> 01:30:48.937
Tell him about the chicken.

1046
01:31:04.536 --> 01:31:06.704
Still nobody knows?

1047
01:31:18.320 --> 01:31:22.137
It was you. You
committed this crime.

1048
01:31:22.220 --> 01:31:24.639
- No, sir.
- But you know who, though.

1049
01:31:24.722 --> 01:31:26.975
- Yes.
- Who?

1050
01:31:27.997 --> 01:31:30.103
Him.

1051
01:31:33.565 --> 01:31:37.485
- He's very gifted.
- Yeah, sure. Bring him over.

1052
01:31:40.280 --> 01:31:44.159
Sir, thank you.

1053
01:31:50.290 --> 01:31:53.084
- Thank you again, Mr Director.
- You're welcome again.

1054
01:31:53.168 --> 01:31:55.649
It's an honour to work for
such a great company.

1055
01:31:55.650 --> 01:31:56.693
It's great to have you.

1056
01:31:56.775 --> 01:31:58.623
I promise to learn
everything there's

1057
01:31:58.624 --> 01:32:00.425
to know about
enamelware production.

1058
01:32:00.426 --> 01:32:01.990
That's great.

1059
01:32:13.563 --> 01:32:17.942
- Hello? Miss Elsa Krause is here.
- I only need five minutes.

1060
01:32:18.026 --> 01:32:20.737
She wants to speak to Mr Director.

1061
01:32:40.256 --> 01:32:42.467
Yes.

1062
01:32:46.721 --> 01:32:49.495
He won't see you.

1063
01:33:19.587 --> 01:33:21.756
Please, sit down.

1064
01:33:24.843 --> 01:33:28.075
- Pernod? Cognac?
- No. No, thank you.

1065
01:33:29.013 --> 01:33:32.559
So, what can I do for you?

1066
01:33:36.583 --> 01:33:39.149
They say that no one dies here.

1067
01:33:39.232 --> 01:33:42.798
They say your factory is a haven.

1068
01:33:44.320 --> 01:33:46.781
They say you are good.

1069
01:33:49.784 --> 01:33:51.995
Who says that?

1070
01:33:52.078 --> 01:33:54.247
Everyone.

1071
01:34:00.545 --> 01:34:03.047
My name is Regina
Perlman, not Elsa Krause.

1072
01:34:03.131 --> 01:34:04.964
I've been living
in Krakow on false

1073
01:34:04.965 --> 01:34:06.697
papers since the ghetto massacre.

1074
01:34:06.780 --> 01:34:08.386
My parents are in Plaszow.

1075
01:34:08.470 --> 01:34:12.974
Their names are Chana
and Jakob Perlman.

1076
01:34:13.057 --> 01:34:14.705
They are older people. They are

1077
01:34:14.706 --> 01:34:16.728
killing older people
now in Plaszow.

1078
01:34:16.769 --> 01:34:21.107
They bury them up in
the forest. Look...

1079
01:34:21.191 --> 01:34:23.902
I don't have any money.

1080
01:34:23.985 --> 01:34:27.426
I borrowed these clothes.

1081
01:34:29.574 --> 01:34:31.659
I'm begging you.

1082
01:34:31.743 --> 01:34:35.559
Please, please bring them here.

1083
01:34:35.643 --> 01:34:38.145
I don't do that.

1084
01:34:38.228 --> 01:34:41.940
You've been misled.
I ask one thing:

1085
01:34:42.024 --> 01:34:45.548
Whether or not a worker
has certain skills.

1086
01:34:45.632 --> 01:34:48.134
My father is an importer,
not a metalworker.

1087
01:34:48.176 --> 01:34:52.722
Such activities are illegal.
You will not entrap me.

1088
01:34:52.806 --> 01:34:56.935
Cry, and I will have you
arrested. I swear to God.

1089
01:35:06.507 --> 01:35:09.280
People die. It's a fact of life.

1090
01:35:09.364 --> 01:35:12.992
He wants to kill everybody? Great.
What am I supposed to do about it?

1091
01:35:13.076 --> 01:35:15.829
Bring everybody over?
Is that what you think?

1092
01:35:15.912 --> 01:35:18.852
Send them over to
Schindler. Send them all.

1093
01:35:18.936 --> 01:35:22.710
His place is a haven, didn't
you know? It's not a factory.

1094
01:35:22.794 --> 01:35:25.046
It's not an enterprise
of any kind.

1095
01:35:25.129 --> 01:35:27.841
It's a haven for
rabbis and orphans...

1096
01:35:27.924 --> 01:35:31.386
and people with no
skills whatsoever.

1097
01:35:33.346 --> 01:35:35.723
You think I don't know
what you're doing?

1098
01:35:35.807 --> 01:35:39.394
You're so quiet all the
time. I know, I know.

1099
01:35:39.477 --> 01:35:42.188
- Are you losing money?
- That's not the point.

1100
01:35:42.272 --> 01:35:44.219
What other point is...

1101
01:35:44.220 --> 01:35:47.548
It's dangerous. It's
dangerous to me.

1102
01:35:50.384 --> 01:35:54.075
You have to understand. Goeth
is under enormous pressure.

1103
01:35:54.159 --> 01:35:57.412
You have to think of
it in his situation.

1104
01:35:57.808 --> 01:36:00.415
He's got this whole place to run.

1105
01:36:00.498 --> 01:36:03.209
He's responsible for everything
here, all these people.

1106
01:36:03.293 --> 01:36:06.629
He's got a lot of
things to worry about.

1107
01:36:06.817 --> 01:36:10.675
And he's got the war which
brings out the worst in people.

1108
01:36:10.758 --> 01:36:14.262
Never the good, always
the bad. Always the bad.

1109
01:36:16.514 --> 01:36:19.027
But in normal
circumstances he wouldn't

1110
01:36:19.028 --> 01:36:21.102
be like this. He'd be all right.

1111
01:36:21.186 --> 01:36:24.647
There'd just be the good
aspects of him which...

1112
01:36:25.461 --> 01:36:28.443
He's a wonderful crook.

1113
01:36:28.526 --> 01:36:32.906
A man who loves good food, good
wine, the ladies, making money...

1114
01:36:32.989 --> 01:36:35.283
Killing.

1115
01:36:35.366 --> 01:36:38.119
He can't enjoy it.

1116
01:36:38.203 --> 01:36:41.289
Bejski told me the other
day, somebody escaped...

1117
01:36:41.372 --> 01:36:44.396
from a work detail
outside the wire.

1118
01:36:44.480 --> 01:36:48.171
Goeth lined up everybody from
the missing man's barracks.

1119
01:36:48.254 --> 01:36:50.001
He shot the man to the left of

1120
01:36:50.002 --> 01:36:52.217
Bejski, the man to
the right of him.

1121
01:36:52.258 --> 01:36:56.179
He walked down the line shooting
every other man with a pistol.

1122
01:37:01.267 --> 01:37:03.770
Twenty-five.

1123
01:37:07.690 --> 01:37:10.094
What do you want
me to do about it?

1124
01:37:10.095 --> 01:37:11.361
Nothing, nothing.

1125
01:37:11.444 --> 01:37:13.780
We're just talking.

1126
01:37:25.667 --> 01:37:27.377
"Perlman."

1127
01:37:29.087 --> 01:37:31.089
Perlman.

1128
01:37:32.006 --> 01:37:33.967
Husband and wife.

1129
01:37:34.050 --> 01:37:38.242
Jakob and Chana Perlman.

1130
01:37:51.109 --> 01:37:54.404
Have Goldberg bring them over.

1131
01:37:56.281 --> 01:37:59.701
Caps off.

1132
01:37:59.784 --> 01:38:01.911
Ready for inspection.

1133
01:38:36.869 --> 01:38:39.167
(GUESTS SINGING
DRUNKENLY IN GERMAN)

1134
01:38:49.563 --> 01:38:53.755
I'm sure this will be better
than those rags, Lisiek.

1135
01:38:53.838 --> 01:38:57.655
Mr Director, I was just helping
Lisiek to find something...

1136
01:38:57.738 --> 01:39:00.762
to clean the stains from
the Commander's bathtub.

1137
01:39:00.845 --> 01:39:03.765
- Go clean it.
- Pardon me, Sir.

1138
01:39:07.352 --> 01:39:10.668
You don't have to
report to me, Helen.

1139
01:39:10.751 --> 01:39:13.650
You know who I am?

1140
01:39:21.741 --> 01:39:25.036
I'm Schindler.

1141
01:39:25.119 --> 01:39:28.644
Of course. I have heard and...

1142
01:39:28.832 --> 01:39:31.981
you have been here before.

1143
01:39:33.753 --> 01:39:36.548
Here, why don't you
keep this some place?

1144
01:39:36.631 --> 01:39:40.135
- Go on, take it.
- I get extra food here.

1145
01:39:40.218 --> 01:39:45.640
Well, if you don't want to eat it,
trade it. Or give it to Lisiek.

1146
01:39:47.725 --> 01:39:50.103
Why not build yourself up?

1147
01:39:54.586 --> 01:39:58.507
My first day here, he beat me...

1148
01:39:58.590 --> 01:40:02.615
because I threw out the
bones from dinner.

1149
01:40:05.660 --> 01:40:10.331
He came down to the basement
at midnight, and he...

1150
01:40:10.415 --> 01:40:13.126
he asked me where they were.

1151
01:40:15.607 --> 01:40:20.216
For his dogs, you understand?

1152
01:40:22.260 --> 01:40:26.556
I said to him, I don't
know how I say this.

1153
01:40:26.639 --> 01:40:30.143
I never could say it
now, I said to him...

1154
01:40:30.226 --> 01:40:33.646
"Why are you beating me?"

1155
01:40:35.899 --> 01:40:39.569
He said, "The reason
I beat you now...

1156
01:40:39.652 --> 01:40:43.886
is because you ask
why I beat you."

1157
01:40:45.450 --> 01:40:48.411
I know your sufferings, Helen.

1158
01:40:50.830 --> 01:40:53.249
It doesn't matter.

1159
01:40:55.001 --> 01:40:57.921
I have accepted them.

1160
01:40:58.004 --> 01:41:00.256
Accepted them?

1161
01:41:02.091 --> 01:41:03.843
One day he will shoot me.

1162
01:41:03.885 --> 01:41:06.763
No, no, no, no, he
won't shoot you.

1163
01:41:06.846 --> 01:41:10.517
I know. I see things.

1164
01:41:10.600 --> 01:41:14.103
We were on the roof on Monday,
young Lisiek and I...

1165
01:41:14.187 --> 01:41:18.107
and we saw the Commander come
out of the front door and...

1166
01:41:18.191 --> 01:41:23.029
and down the steps by the patio
right there below us and...

1167
01:41:23.112 --> 01:41:28.034
and there on the steps he
drew his gun and he...

1168
01:41:28.117 --> 01:41:31.454
shot a woman who was passing by.

1169
01:41:32.539 --> 01:41:35.771
A woman carrying a bundle.
Through the throat.

1170
01:41:35.854 --> 01:41:39.546
Just-Just a woman on her
way somewhere, you know.

1171
01:41:39.629 --> 01:41:43.341
She was no fatter or thinner...

1172
01:41:43.424 --> 01:41:45.844
or slower or faster
than anyone else...

1173
01:41:45.927 --> 01:41:51.036
and I couldn't guess
what had she done.

1174
01:41:54.435 --> 01:41:57.897
The more you see of
the Commander...

1175
01:41:57.981 --> 01:42:03.215
the more you see there is no set
rules that you can live by.

1176
01:42:03.507 --> 01:42:06.194
You can't say to yourself, "If I

1177
01:42:06.195 --> 01:42:09.388
follow these rules,
I will be safe."

1178
01:42:11.828 --> 01:42:16.082
He won't shoot you because
he enjoys you too much.

1179
01:42:16.270 --> 01:42:20.357
He enjoys you so much he won't
even let you wear the star.

1180
01:42:20.441 --> 01:42:25.779
He doesn't want anyone else to
know, it's a Jew he's enjoying.

1181
01:42:28.574 --> 01:42:32.067
He shot the woman
from the steps...

1182
01:42:32.068 --> 01:42:35.560
because she meant nothing to him.

1183
01:42:35.873 --> 01:42:42.004
She was one of a series neither
offending or pleasing him.

1184
01:42:44.486 --> 01:42:47.655
But you, Helen.

1185
01:42:51.534 --> 01:42:56.810
It's all right. It's not
that kind of a kiss.

1186
01:43:01.732 --> 01:43:03.630
Thank you.

1187
01:43:08.426 --> 01:43:10.303
Here.

1188
01:43:16.163 --> 01:43:18.645
Right, the wine.

1189
01:43:25.568 --> 01:43:29.301
Wonderful party, Amon. Thank you.

1190
01:43:37.038 --> 01:43:40.479
Why do you drink that motor oil?

1191
01:43:40.562 --> 01:43:43.336
I send you good
stuff all the time.

1192
01:43:43.419 --> 01:43:47.340
Your liver's going to explode
like a hand grenade.

1193
01:43:47.423 --> 01:43:50.176
You know, I look at you...

1194
01:43:50.260 --> 01:43:52.762
I watch you.

1195
01:43:55.140 --> 01:43:56.516
You're never drunk.

1196
01:43:57.538 --> 01:44:00.207
Oh, that's...

1197
01:44:00.395 --> 01:44:03.377
that's real control.

1198
01:44:03.565 --> 01:44:05.942
Control is power.

1199
01:44:06.776 --> 01:44:09.279
That's power.

1200
01:44:12.907 --> 01:44:16.995
Is that why they fear us?

1201
01:44:18.017 --> 01:44:21.749
We have the fucking power to
kill, that's why they fear us.

1202
01:44:21.937 --> 01:44:25.753
They fear us because we have
the power to kill arbitrarily.

1203
01:44:25.837 --> 01:44:27.985
A man commits a crime,
he should know better.

1204
01:44:28.068 --> 01:44:30.717
We have him killed, and we
feel pretty good about it.

1205
01:44:30.800 --> 01:44:35.034
Or we kill him ourselves
and we feel even better.

1206
01:44:36.139 --> 01:44:39.058
That's not power, though.

1207
01:44:39.142 --> 01:44:43.876
That's justice. It's
different than power.

1208
01:44:46.232 --> 01:44:51.404
Power is when we have every
justification to kill...

1209
01:44:51.488 --> 01:44:54.073
and we don't.

1210
01:44:54.157 --> 01:44:56.930
You think that's power?

1211
01:44:58.786 --> 01:45:02.040
That's what the emperors had.
A man stole something...

1212
01:45:02.123 --> 01:45:03.687
he's brought in
before the emperor...

1213
01:45:03.771 --> 01:45:07.921
he throws himself down on the
ground, he begs for mercy.

1214
01:45:08.004 --> 01:45:11.549
He knows he's going to die.

1215
01:45:13.468 --> 01:45:17.701
And the emperor, pardons him.

1216
01:45:18.118 --> 01:45:22.331
This worthless man.
He lets him go.

1217
01:45:24.854 --> 01:45:27.857
I think you are drunk.

1218
01:45:28.900 --> 01:45:31.903
That's power, Amon.

1219
01:45:31.986 --> 01:45:35.949
That, is power.

1220
01:45:42.997 --> 01:45:46.918
Amon the good.

1221
01:45:48.837 --> 01:45:51.881
I pardon you.

1222
01:45:59.139 --> 01:46:00.244
What do they want?

1223
01:46:00.327 --> 01:46:01.822
I don't know, but they're in my

1224
01:46:01.823 --> 01:46:03.706
office right now
reviewing our books.

1225
01:46:03.789 --> 01:46:07.147
As my accountant, tell me,
should I be alarmed...

1226
01:46:07.230 --> 01:46:09.884
that the auditors are
reviewing my books?

1227
01:46:09.920 --> 01:46:11.541
Or have you done
your job properly?

1228
01:46:11.542 --> 01:46:12.652
You needn't be alarmed.

1229
01:46:12.735 --> 01:46:14.946
I needn't be alarmed.

1230
01:46:19.114 --> 01:46:20.114
I'm sorry, sir.

1231
01:46:20.115 --> 01:46:22.308
Do you know how much
this saddle is worth?

1232
01:46:22.370 --> 01:46:25.769
Do you know how much it costs?

1233
01:46:29.794 --> 01:46:31.796
All right.

1234
01:46:33.444 --> 01:46:35.550
All right.

1235
01:46:38.887 --> 01:46:42.578
Stern, what the hell are you
doing following me around?

1236
01:46:51.795 --> 01:46:54.652
Barracks one, eleven...

1237
01:46:54.736 --> 01:46:57.280
fifteen and thirty-two...

1238
01:46:57.363 --> 01:47:00.471
apply to inspection area.

1239
01:47:29.521 --> 01:47:32.127
She was smoking on the job.

